- per test that needed changes in the code generation evaluate the code quality according to /doc/claude/CODE.md

Start with a separate testing suite:
- When something fails in this suite the normal way of working is creating new tests in /tests/ to repair the problem with full debugging enabled.
- Move the relevant tests from /tests/ to this new suite that only contains .loft files.
- Create shorter files with clear categories.
- Include missing cases: for example writing and reading files with data types that are not yet tested.
- Make asserts that clearly show which test fails, it is not important to show any details outside what fails.
- Then create a Makefile target that runs all the defined tests in the suite.
- Do not generate /code/*.txt files or rust code during running this new suite. This is for performance and generally less stress on the tools.

Identify less important tests in /tests/ and let them only live inside the testing suite.

